-- Allianz Plans to Bid for Groupama Unit, FT Deutschland Reports
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-03-08T19:42:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/allianz-plans-to-bid-for-groupama-unit-ft-deutschland-reports.html
Allianz SE (ALV)  is preparing a bid for
 Groupama SA (GPAS) ’s GAN Eurocourtage unit and may offer a price in the
“high three-digit millions” of euros or more, Financial Times
Deutschland reported, citing unidentified people close to the
 insurance industry .  Allianz is more interested in acquiring the business than
 Aviva Plc (AV/)  and French insurance group Covea, which are also
potential suitors, the Hamburg-based newspaper said in an e-
mailed summary of an article to be published tomorrow.  QBE
Insurance Group Ltd. (QBE)  is no longer among bidders for the
business, FT Deutschland reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
